[3] PAHO/WHO: epidemiological update
Date: Thu 4 Aug 2022
Source: PAHO/WHO
https://www.paho.org/en/documents/epidemiological-update-monkeypox-children-adolescents-and-pregnant-women-4-august-2022


Between 1 Jan and 2 Aug 2022, a total of 25 022 confirmed cases, including 9 deaths, were reported from 83 Member States in 6 World Health Organization (WHO) Regions. The 9 fatal cases were reported in Brazil (1), India (1), Nigeria (3), Spain (2), and the Central African Republic (2).

During the last 7 days there was an increase of 33.5% and 70% in the number of reported cases globally and in the WHO Region of the Americas, respectively.

Of the reported cases for which information on age is available (n=16 969), 96 are among minors (<18 years old); of these, 61% are male. Regarding age, 51% (49 cases) are aged 11-17 years, and 26% (25 cases) are children aged 0-4 years. No deaths have been reported in these age groups. Of the 33 confirmed cases for which hospitalization data is available, 42% required hospitalization for isolation or treatment. None of the cases had any comorbidities.

