[6] Thailand
Date: Sun 7 Aug 2022
Source: Bangkok Post [abridged, edited]
https://www.bangkokpost.com/thailand/special-reports/2363114/emerging-monkeypox-threat


Thailand has now found 4 monkeypox patients, including the 1st Thai woman last Friday [5 Aug 2022]. Given the apparent rise in infections, the Ministry of Public Health has come under pressure to formulate control.

The 1st monkeypox case was confirmed on 21 Jul [2022] in Phuket with a 27-year-old Nigerian man, followed by a 47-year-old Thai man on 28 Jul [2022] in Bangkok. The infection of a 25-year-old German man was confirmed on 3 Aug [2022].

The ministry believes more cases are likely to emerge in Thailand but says spread of the disease is likely to be much less extensive than for COVID-19.

[Byline: Apinya Wipatayotin and Poramet Tangsathaporn]

